# Performance Critical Design

## Must
- Use data-oriented layouts and memory-access patterns in performance-sensitive paths.
- Require profiling evidence for changes to hot paths (CPU/GPU).
- Track median and P95 performance deltas against accepted baseline.
- Keep allocation behavior explicit in critical loops and frame/step paths.

## Must Not
- Do not claim performance gains without benchmark evidence on the approved perf runner class.
- Do not accept hidden regressions masked by workload changes.

## Required Evidence
- Before/after profiling artifact and baseline delta summary.
